13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Results: Healing as a % of Warrior HPs (40-60)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Chloroblast on a 55+ tank is half a red bubble if that. Its mana / healing ratio better then SH does not make up for the fact that I can not be a solo healer for a group without a slower (when a tank is loosing more then half a red per 3 seconds).<br>
</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Druids are not supposed to be solo healers. We are backup healers. This is where everyone is getting off track imo.<br>
<br>
Our healing is meant primarly to reduce downtime between fights and secondary as a stop gap for clerics when the whole group is taking damage (AEs, multiple mobs) and to keep the cleric alive of course.<br>
<br>
The problem I see is people want to be able to heal a group on their own and we are not set up for that role imo.<br>
<br>
BTW - priest does not mean cleric. Being a priest class should not imply cleric level healing. <p><br>
<center> <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1146">Loegan Wolfheart </A> <br>
