If you only have slightly more downtime than a cleric AND can succor in an emergency, then why is a cleric preferred?<br>
<br>
Your own statements make my argument for me. We should not be able to do the job of a cleric. They gave up the variety we have to specialize in healing, so no way we should be able to fill their shoes. I am sure a cleric wants to be more than just a rezz machine, which is all they would be if druids could heal as close to a clerics level as you say.<br>
